               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390304-name-773" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390304-name-773" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390304-name-773" type="surname" value="CHAPMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390304-name-773" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN CHAPMAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a glover, and live in King William-street, Strand. On the 26th of February, about a quarter-past ten o'clock in the morning, I left my shop for a few minutes, and on looking from my back parlour I saw the prisoner leaving the shop with something bulky under his coat—I ran after him into the Strand—he found I was pretty close to him, and he dropped from his coat twenty-three handkerchiefs and a scarf which had been taken from my shop window—I took them up, and called "Stop thief"—a person brought him back in a few minutes—these things cost me about 5.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390304-name-774" type="witnessName">
